                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/207</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-26T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 22. Oil pipe line. General Carranza informed me personally
                    the pipe line in question would not directly or indirectly affect the oil rights
                    of American citizens; that it was intended to be a public carrier to transport
                    oil to the coast for any individual or company that paid for the service.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
